args:
When Emile loses his temper and activates the
android commander Laxi, she goes berserk and
attacks friend and foe alike. This causes the
dormant androids to reactivate, forcing the
prince and his friends to work with Mascula
in order to halt their rampage.
Now! Counterattack! Push the enemy back!
What in the blazes are you idiots DOING?!\nI thought you had them cornered!
F-forgive us, sire! We failed to take into\naccount the numerous abandoned\nbuildings in the ruins of the town!
The New Alberian Army is forcing us into\nhouse-to-house fighting, which negates\nthe advantage of our superior numbers.
So send in the androids already!\nSurely they won't be so easily cowed!
Er, yes, sire. The thing is, the lead android\nseems to have...taken up with the enemy\nand shut down the rest of them somehow.
Rrrrgh! That traitorous pile of scrap!
Fine, then. If he won't do the job,\nI'll just find someone who will.\nBring me the last android!
B-but sir, if that android were to betray\nus as Mascula did—

Today is no day for the feckless talk of
cowards! Now shut up and do as I say
before I have you clapped in irons and
tossed into the sea!
Awaken, android! Crush the traitor and his\nnew friend, {player_name}!
Oh, this is NOT good! Graaaagh!
Beginning suppression of this location.\nInitiating termination of all enemies.
Sire, the imperial forces approaching the\nwestern ruins appear to have withdrawn.\nWe should be okay for a while.
Good. If we keep this up and buy ourselves\ntime to move the villagers to safety,\nthings might actually work out.

And yet, this is not the time to rest easy.
If the androids were to start moving again,
we could easily find our backs against
the wall once more.
Yeah, I mean, Mascula told us he stopped\n'em all, but can we really trust that guy?
I don't think he's a bad...uh, android,\nbut that also doesn't mean he's our\nfriend, necessarily.
I agree. After all, from his perspective,\nwe're still trying to harm people.
Never thought we'd run into someone\nwho's even more of a goody two-shoes\nthan us. What a world.
We can think about the pros and cons of\nfighting later. The important thing now is\nthat Mascula stopped the other androids.
Yeah, but couldn't he have...I dunno.\nMade 'em LEAVE? It's creepy as hell\nto see 'em all standin' around like that.

Perhaps there is a way to further disable
them while they are in this resting state.
We could attempt to remove their arms
and legs, for example.
I'm not sure Mascula would like us doing\nsomething so drastic. And right now,\nwe need to keep him as an ally.

Yeah, probably best not to do anything
that seems like a betrayal of his trust.
Plus, I'd feel kinda weird deboning
helpless androids like that.
Your Highness, I bring news!\nA strange android has been sighted\non the eastern front!
Strange in that it does not seem to be\ndistinguishing friend from foe, and is\ninstead attacking everyone on sight.
Mascula didn't distinguish between\nfriend or foe either!

Yes, but his ultimate goal seemed to be
one of peace. This new android is cutting
down any who get in its way without
mercy or quarter.
Our lead garrison has already sustained\nheavy losses, which have been matched\nby imperial casualties. Furthermore—
Somebody wanna explain what in the\nblue heck is going on here?!
So it's happening here as well...
The units on the eastern front also\nrecently began moving again.
Do you think it has something to do\nwith that new android?
I don't know. However, I imagine Mascula\nhas more information, so I have sent for\nhim with all speed.
Got it. In the meantime, I'm heading out\nto the eastern front. Ranzal, I'll need you\nto stay and handle things here.
Sure, boss. And apologies to Mascula\nor whatever, but if these fools decide to\nattack again, we'll wipe the floor with 'em!
That android really is\ngoing after everyone...
Is she the reason all the others\nhave started moving again?
Yes. I can't stop her orders.
Then I'll just have to stop HER.
I will. I must. It is what I was made for!
You appear to have sustained damage.\nDon't worry. I'll fix you.
Laxi, stop! Please! Maestro would be\nso sad to see us doing this!
Yes, Maestro. Why did he give us\nhearts if not to use them here?
Well, THAT was a totally normal thing\nthat just happened.
Mascula may have driven her off,\nbut the other androids are still coming!
Laxi is the commander. If I can stop her,\nI can stop all the androids.
I think we should give Mascula's plan\na shot, {player_name}!
We're only going to suffer more losses\nif we keep fighting like this. Might as well\ntake a chance on trusting Mascula.
All right, Mascula. I'll trust you on this.
